  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when the children of Israel cried unto the Lord,.... Towards the close of the eight years' bondage, as it may be supposed, groaning under the oppressive taxes laid upon them, and the bondage they were brought into: and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the Lord raised up a deliverer to the children of Israel; he heard their cry, and sent them a saviour, whose spirit he stirred up, and whom he qualified for this service: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who delivered them; out of the hands of the king of Mesopotamia, and freed them from his oppressions: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "even Othniel, the son of Kenaz, Caleb's younger brother; the same that took Debir, and married Achsah, the daughter of Caleb, Judges 1:12; who now very probably was a man in years. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "even Othniel, the son of Kenaz, Caleb's younger brother; the same that took Debir, and married Achsah, the daughter of Caleb, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 1:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; who now very probably was a man in years. ",
            "children": []
          },
